SIMPLE: blinding
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Blinding
<hw>Blind"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Making blind or as if blind;
depriving of sight or of understanding; obscuring; <as>as,
<ex>blinding</ex> tears; <ex>blinding</ex> snow</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blinding</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Blinding
<hw>Blind"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A thin coating of sand and fine
gravel over a newly paved road. See <er>Blind</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>,
4.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blindly</ent>⟦br⟧
